data.meta_description: Braddock, PA: Braddock Avenue Books, Oct. 19, 2021. Described as a “…collective of love and longing, of disappointment and loss and, ultimately, faith” William Lychack , John Vanderslice’s new novel, Nous Nous, lays out a dark vision of the awful human consequences a community faces when one man’s small world is shattered.
